.TH "drm_mode_crtc_set_gamma_size" 9 "drm_mode_crtc_set_gamma_size" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_mode_crtc_set_gamma_size \- set the gamma table size
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_mode_crtc_set_gamma_size
.BI "(struct drm_crtc *crtc "  ","
.BI "int gamma_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "crtc" 12
CRTC to set the gamma table size for
.IP "gamma_size" 12
size of the gamma table
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Drivers which support gamma tables should set this to the supported gamma
table size when initializing the CRTC. Currently the drm core only supports a
fixed gamma table size.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero on success, negative errno on failure.
